    <p><em>This page describes the cookies and similar technologies used on this website, in accordance with the EU ePrivacy directive and the Luxembourg law of 30 May 2005.</em></p>

    <h2>What is a cookie?</h2>
    <p>A cookie is a small text file stored on your device by your browser when you visit a website. Cookies allow websites to remember information about your visit.</p>

    <h2>Cookies used on this site</h2>

    <h3>Strictly necessary (no consent required)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>cookieConsent</strong> (localStorage) — remembers your cookie preference. Duration: permanent until you clear your browser storage.</li>
      <li><strong>samLang</strong> (localStorage) — remembers your selected language. Duration: permanent until cleared.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Functional / analytics / marketing</h3>
    <p><em>Currently none. If we introduce analytics or marketing cookies in the future, you will be asked for consent before any non-essential cookie is set.</em></p>

    <h2>Third-party services</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Google Fonts</strong> — font files served from fonts.googleapis.com. Google may log the IP address of requesting browsers. No cookies are set.</li>
      <li><strong>Google Maps</strong> (embedded on the contact section) — sets cookies once you load the map. Consult <a href="https://policies.google.com/" rel="noopener">Google's privacy policy</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>WhatsApp</strong> — clicking the WhatsApp button opens wa.me which is subject to Meta's policies.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How to manage cookies</h2>
    <p>You can accept or refuse cookies through our cookie banner when first visiting the site. You can also clear cookies and site data via your browser settings at any time.</p>

